      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but isn't \"broken grammar\" a bit of an unfair way to put it? language experts usually say things like AAVE have their own consistent rules. if a student is clearly brilliant and has a great grasp of the subject matter, but just expresses it through their native dialect, does that really mean they lack the intellectual capacity for research? or is the issue just that the \"standard\" is set to a specific way of speaking?",
